<br>
You set a negative ton with both your thread title and your first sentence,  &quot;I dont know about you, but any bard post level 30 that does not have or use this everquest.allakhazam.com/...spell=1948 is a freaken idiot&quot;<br>
<br>
Although I don't like your attitude and the fact that you call all bards idiots that don't adhere to your limited knowledge of our job, I will try to list constructive uses for amp.<br>
<br>
Amplification has a bonus that goes up by level and is roughly the same as our epic at 60th (about 80 percent to the base).  The commonly used songs that this influences the most are:<br>
1. Our single resist songs<br>
2. Our DS's (which are actually single resist songs)<br>
3. 32 mana song<br>
The haste and slow portions of voice-based songs are NOT increased at all by amplification.<br>
<br>
32 mana song cannot be &quot;twisted&quot; with other songs because the effect stops the second the singing stops, whereas the bulk of our songs last up to 18 seconds later.  This coupled with the fact that it has a very short range of effect makes it highly undesireable to use during combat.  <br>
<br>
So basically you are asking a bard to mem amp and 32 clarity for downtime (and hogging 2 spell slots in the process).  Our hands get very tired from repetitive motion and downtime is the one moment of relaxation for our fingers/wrists.  While in theory it would be great to have a bard twist 24-7, in practice this is unreasonable.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
