<br>
But anyway.  I can only come up with one explanation for Stacy's line of reasoning here, and based on that, I have a great deal of sympathy for her (female name, I'm using female pronouns).  It appears that Stacy has grown up in a home which is very verbally abusive; where it's appropriate to insult people while you're trying to get or give information.  By responding to her in the same tone she started this with, we're not helping her integrate into normal society.<br>
<br>
As for the whole &quot;Bards are lazy! No, Druids are lazy!&quot; argument...<br>
<br>
There aren't lazy classes, only lazy people.  Lazy people rarely get bards past about 25th level.  When you start getting fear and charm and it gets really complicated, the lazy person gets turned off and does something else.  But, lazy people are able to play druids into the 50's without much problem.  It is certainly possible and even easy to be versatile and bring a lot to a group with a druid; however, the lazy *person* elects to root-rot or quad-kite his way through the levels, and then wonders why no one wants to group with him.<br>
<br>
Therefore, druids get a reputation for laziness, because lazy people are drawn to the class because of its utility.  Warriors may also draw lazy people, but somehow, it's less obvious if they do.<br>
<br>
Bards don't get a reputation for laziness unless you deal a lot with AFK manabards.  I don't have room for hotkeys for all the things I do... &quot;Mezzed %t&quot; &quot;Slowed/snared %t&quot; &quot;OOSed %t, fire at will&quot; I end up being very curt because I'm too busy keeping it going.<br>
<br>
As for bards pulling, lots of folks have said good things about it, but let's break it down real simple-like.  Bards are the *only* class that can do footspeed, snare, lull (we have a single-target lull song that works near as well as Harmony, and works indoors too), have ranged attacks, can cancel magic (great now that SK mobs are doing the damage shield thing a lot), invis, lev, and have the HP/AC to get back to the group without dying.  About the only thing that helps a puller that we *don't* have is FD.  At 60 bards even get DA.  *That* is why the bard is pulling... because they are the single best-equipped class for it.<br>
<br>
If you want to know what situations a song works well in, or why people don't use a song more often, best thing to do is to actually ask it in the form of a question on The Concert Hall or eqdiva.  You'll get some great, informative answers from some really nice people.  But spit in people's faces, and don't be surprised if they spit back. <p><a href = http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=282419><img src=http://www.boondock.org/images/xelene_ezboard.jpg></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarueivywood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darue Ivywood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 727<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/16/02 11:59:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3630.topic&index=98>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I am a druid at heart, who needs invis. Get in trouble, load your drum and haul ass out of there. Screw casting invis, waste of time. I could be half way across zone before I could get it loaded and casted. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
